social_posts.post_text: Ribcage Study #Sketchbook #Anatomy #Drawing

Working on some banner art. Looking forward to a lot of fun things in 2023, starting with setting up a Patreon page. I won't give away too much info right now since I'm still figuring out what I want to make out of it. But keep an eye out in the nest few weeks for more details!

#sketchbook #drawing #scifigirls
Medic. I imagine those tubes glowing up like ambulance lights haha. #sketchbook

Harpy. There is something beautiful and frightening about her. Her warm elegance fights with her cold artificiality. Seemingly delicate and powerful all at once. One thing is certain though, she is unpredictable.

Didn't really have a plan for this character, just started drawing and figured it out along the way. It's funny to see the kind of design language and shapes I fall back on when I don't have a plan in mind.
Very protective pew pew battle suit. #scifi #sketchbook
I liked this design so I painted her up. I'm putting together a timelapse video of the painting process and it should be up on youtube in the next couple days:)
Big Gun. The process for drawing the coat and gun is up on youtube:)
Some portrait studies I did a couple weeks ago. The full process with commentary is up on youtube for your enjoyment! Cheers:)

My first Patreon livestream went really well today and I got some more work done on this illustration. More WIPs and variants are also available on my Patreon:) This piece is still in progress but we're starting to get somewhere with it!
Reincarnated Character Design. The whole drawing process will be up on youtube shortly! More WIPs available on my Patreon, link in my bio.
Finished illustrating Jessy this week:) PSDs, step-by-step breakdowns and brushes are all available for the Workshop Tier on my Patreon.
Scarred. A quick 3h painting I did last night. The whole process is up on youtube. I know she kinda looks like Scarlett Johansson but that wasn't intentional haha.
Anatomy Study. Timelapse process is up on my youtube channel.
Battlesuit. Which colour is your favorite? PSD and process breakdown of this illustration is up on my patreon!

Portrait Study. My latest Workshop Livestream on Patreon covers fixing a wonky portrait and I used this one as an example. We talked about how to approach self-criticism and trying to fix our mistakes. Every week I cover new topics to grow and improve your art!

Portrait sketches. The real-time process for these portrait sketches are up on youtube. Enjoy!

This month I challenged my patrons to a portrait showdown! 3 heads, 3-ish weeks left to draw them:) You can join too and learn more a portrait sketching and painting over on my patreon. Let's draw some heads!
Handsome fella portrait study. This was done for a workshop livestream in light on this month's patreon art challenge.
Renegade character design. The full process with commentary is up on youtube for your enjoyment! Cheers

Jessy Lighting Study. I painted this illustration of my character Jessy in an action pose and practiced some different lighting schemes while I was at it. I uploaded a youtube video talking about my whole layer setup if you're interested!
Getting in the Halloween spirit! 🦇
